{'entities': [{'id': 720043, 'name': 'Region Merge', 'description': "Region Merge is a process in TiKV, part of the TiDB ecosystem, designed to combine adjacent or small regions into larger ones. This operation aims to optimize performance, improve storage efficiency, and enhance query speed by reducing the number of regions that need to be accessed. It is particularly useful after operations like dropping or truncating large amounts of data, which can leave behind many empty or small regions. By default enabled since TiDB v3.0, Region Merge triggers writing in-memory pessimistic locks to disk and replicates them to other replicas. However, it can also be controlled through the merge_option attribute, allowing administrators to set it to 'allow' or 'deny' as needed. The feature addresses issues like slow query performance post-deletion and handles scenarios involving large numbers of empty regions. While Region Merge offers significant benefits, it is not without risks; potential issues include panics and unexpected peer destruction if the target region is invalid or if the target peer is replaced with a destroyed peer. Additionally, this process may involve writing in-memory pessimistic locks to disk and replication. A panic issue that could occur when the source peer catches up logs by snapshot during the merge process has been fixed."}, {'id': 363249, 'name': 'Table Attributes', 'description': 'Attributes used to control the Region merge behavior of a table or partition, influencing how tables operate by managing aspects like region merging. These attributes can be set using the ALTER TABLE statement and are reflected in the information_schema.attributes table.'}, {'id': 390041, 'name': 'TiKV', 'description': 'TiKV processes `DECIMAL` arithmetic multiplication truncation, which can lead to inconsistencies with TiDB. A fix in TiKV addressed the decimal operations overflow issue.'}, {'id': 810019, 'name': 'TiKV', 'description': 'TiKV is a distributed transactional key-value storage engine serving as the foundational layer for TiDB, a distributed SQL database. It uses RocksDB for local storage and Raft for replication, ensuring data consistency through log replication. Features include batch split support, row count-based region splitting, expression pushdowns including string, aggregation, encryption, and cast functions, and support for both optimistic and pessimistic transactions. TiKV dynamically adjusts resource quotas, handles backup/restore operations, supports encryption using AES or SM4, and can operate as a standalone key-value store (RawKV) without TiDB. It is used in TiDB Cloud and self-hosted platforms, deployable with or without TiFlash. Sufficient resources are recommended for optimal performance, and disk sharing is not advised. TiKV is scalable in the Dedicated Tier on AWS for clusters created post-December 31, 2022. Additionally, TiKV introduces Region Merge, Raw DeleteRange API, and improved read performance using ReadPool.'}, {'id': 900146, 'name': 'Grafana Monitoring Dashboard', 'description': 'A monitoring dashboard used to visualize various metrics related to TiDB, PD, and TiKV. It can be used to monitor the merged operator, disk performance, and etcd performance. Additionally, it visualizes DM monitoring metrics.'}, {'id': 46092, 'name': 'Lagging Region Peer', 'description': 'A replica of a region that is behind the leader in terms of data replication.'}, {'id': 720079, 'name': 'Snapshot', 'description': 'A Snapshot is a consistent view of data at a specific time, used for backup purposes and creating replicas. It captures the state of data in TiFlash tables and can be generated through a full table scan from TiKV. Snapshots are managed across different layers (Stable, Delta, Meta) with associated metrics tracking their count, lifetime, thread IDs, and tracing IDs. They support concurrent operations like Region merge and ConfChange without affecting the database state but may cause issues when applied alongside multiple DDL operations in TiFlash.'}, {'id': 46094, 'name': 'ConfChange', 'description': 'An operation that changes the configuration of a region.'}, {'id': 54754, 'name': 'DELETE Operation', 'description': 'An operation to remove data from a database table.'}], 'relationships': [{'id': 32898, 'relationship': 'Region merge behavior can be controlled using table attributes.', 'doc_link': 'https://docs.pingcap.com/tidb/v8.1/troubleshoot-hot-spot-issues', 'source_entity': {'id': 720043, 'name': 'Region Merge'}, 'target_entity': {'id': 363249, 'name': 'Table Attributes'}}, {'id': 37726, 'relationship': 'Region merge is an operation performed by TiKV.', 'doc_link': 'https://docs.pingcap.com/tidb/v8.1/release-7.5.1', 'source_entity': {'id': 720043, 'name': 'Region Merge'}, 'target_entity': {'id': 390041, 'name': 'TiKV'}}, {'id': 41777, 'relationship': '`Region Merge` is a process in TiKV.', 'doc_link': 'https://docs.pingcap.com/tidb/v8.1/release-3.0.13', 'source_entity': {'id': 720043, 'name': 'Region Merge'}, 'target_entity': {'id': 810019, 'name': 'TiKV'}}, {'id': 35374, 'relationship': 'The merged operator can be monitored using the Grafana dashboard.', 'doc_link': 'https://docs.pingcap.com/tidb/v8.1/tidb-troubleshooting-map', 'source_entity': {'id': 720043, 'name': 'Region Merge'}, 'target_entity': {'id': 900146, 'name': 'Grafana Monitoring Dashboard'}}, {'id': 43723, 'relationship': 'A bug fix in TiDB 5.2.4 addresses possible metadata corruption caused by region merge on a lagging region peer.', 'doc_link': 'https://docs.pingcap.com/tidb/v8.1/release-5.2.4', 'source_entity': {'id': 720043, 'name': 'Region Merge'}, 'target_entity': {'id': 46092, 'name': 'Lagging Region Peer'}}, {'id': 43731, 'relationship': 'A bug fix in TiDB 5.2.4 addresses a panic issue occurring when region merge, ConfChange, and Snapshot happen concurrently.', 'doc_link': 'https://docs.pingcap.com/tidb/v8.1/release-5.2.4', 'source_entity': {'id': 720043, 'name': 'Region Merge'}, 'target_entity': {'id': 720079, 'name': 'Snapshot'}}, {'id': 43726, 'relationship': 'A bug fix in TiDB 5.2.4 addresses a panic issue occurring when region merge, ConfChange, and Snapshot happen concurrently.', 'doc_link': 'https://docs.pingcap.com/tidb/v8.1/release-5.2.4', 'source_entity': {'id': 720043, 'name': 'Region Merge'}, 'target_entity': {'id': 46094, 'name': 'ConfChange'}}, {'id': 52047, 'relationship': 'Region Merge can improve query speed after large data deletions.', 'doc_link': 'https://docs.pingcap.com/tidb/v8.1/sql-faq', 'source_entity': {'id': 720043, 'name': 'Region Merge'}, 'target_entity': {'id': 54754, 'name': 'DELETE Operation'}}]}

