{'entities': [{'id': 56463, 'name': 'Dual Network Interface Cards (NICs)', 'description': 'A computer hardware component that allows a computer to connect to a network.'}, {'id': 510050, 'name': 'TiDB Dashboard', 'description': 'TiDB Dashboard is a web-based interface for monitoring, managing, and analyzing TiDB clusters. It provides a user-friendly platform accessible via a web browser, offering features such as visual execution plans, monitoring pages, and query analysis tools. Introduced in TiDB v4.0, the dashboard was moved to a dedicated monitoring node in v6.2.0 to enhance stability and reduce impact on PD nodes. Key functionalities include performance tuning, cluster configuration, troubleshooting, and support for features like OIDC SSO.'}, {'id': 360871, 'name': 'tiup cluster', 'description': 'TiUP Cluster is a command-line tool and component of TiUP that supports deploying and managing multiple TiDB clusters on a single control machine. It is designed for production environments and provides functionalities for managing TiDB clusters. The tool also offers help information for users via the command line interface. Currently, deploying TiDB with dual NICs using tiup cluster presents a challenge for accessing TiDB Dashboard through the secondary NIC, which requires a workaround using a reverse proxy.'}, {'id': 362573, 'name': 'tiup playground', 'description': "Tiup Playground is a command-line tool for quickly deploying a local TiDB cluster for testing and development purposes. It allows users to start a TiDB cluster locally, specify the TiDB version, and determine the number of instances for each component. The tool is designed for quick deployment and cleanup, with data being removed after the test deployment unless persistence is specified using the '--tag' option. Tiup Playground supports Mac computers with Apple M1 chips and has a limitation when deploying TiDB with dual NICs, where access to the TiDB Dashboard via the second NIC is restricted. A reverse proxy is recommended to overcome this limitation."}, {'id': 363313, 'name': 'Reverse Proxy', 'description': 'A reverse proxy is a server that sits in front of one or more backend servers, intercepting client requests and forwarding them to the appropriate backend server. It is commonly used to securely expose services like the TiDB Dashboard from internal networks to external users on a different port. The use of a reverse proxy can impact access to the TiDB Dashboard when multiple PD instances are deployed. It is recommended to provide services with the /dashboard prefix and restrict access to specified paths only for security reasons. Tools such as HAProxy or NGINX can be configured to match customized path prefixes.'}], 'relationships': [{'id': 53775, 'relationship': 'When TiDB Dashboard is deployed with dual NICs, it cannot be accessed using another NIC.', 'doc_link': 'https://docs.pingcap.com/tidb/v8.1/dashboard-faq', 'source_entity': {'id': 56463, 'name': 'Dual Network Interface Cards (NICs)'}, 'target_entity': {'id': 510050, 'name': 'TiDB Dashboard'}}, {'id': 53777, 'relationship': 'The dual NIC issue with TiDB Dashboard is not currently solvable when deployed using tiup cluster.', 'doc_link': 'https://docs.pingcap.com/tidb/v8.1/dashboard-faq', 'source_entity': {'id': 360871, 'name': 'tiup cluster'}, 'target_entity': {'id': 56463, 'name': 'Dual Network Interface Cards (NICs)'}}, {'id': 53778, 'relationship': 'The dual NIC issue with TiDB Dashboard is not currently solvable when deployed using tiup playground.', 'doc_link': 'https://docs.pingcap.com/tidb/v8.1/dashboard-faq', 'source_entity': {'id': 362573, 'name': 'tiup playground'}, 'target_entity': {'id': 56463, 'name': 'Dual Network Interface Cards (NICs)'}}, {'id': 53760, 'relationship': 'A reverse proxy is recommended for accessing TiDB Dashboard through a different NIC when dual NICs are used.', 'doc_link': 'https://docs.pingcap.com/tidb/v8.1/dashboard-faq', 'source_entity': {'id': 510050, 'name': 'TiDB Dashboard'}, 'target_entity': {'id': 363313, 'name': 'Reverse Proxy'}}]}

